URGENT FIX: Ad Network dropdown not switching fields properly

In the current "Add New Video Ad" form:

1. When "MyAdCash" is selected → 
   - Hide "Script URL" field
   - Show only "Zone ID" field
   - On Save → auto-generate this exact MyAdCash code and save in rawEmbedCode:

<script src="//acscdn.com/script/aclib.js"></script>
<script>
  var aclib = aclib || {}; 
  aclib.cmd = aclib.cmd || [];
  aclib.cmd.push(function(){
    aclib.renderAd({
      zoneId: "INSERT_ZONE_ID_HERE",
      width: "100%",
      height: "100vh"
    });
  });
</script>

   (replace INSERT_ZONE_ID_HERE with actual zone ID)

2. When "Custom" is selected → 
   - Hide Zone ID and Script URL
   - Show big TextArea "Paste Full Ad Code Here"

3. When "HilltopAds" is selected → keep old behavior (Zone ID + auto generate)

4. When "PropellerAds" or any new network added later → treat as Custom (show TextArea)

Fix field visibility instantly when dropdown changes – no page reload needed.

FINAL FIX: Generate correct MyAdCash code – no more HilltopAds fallback

In "Add New Video Ad" form:

When "MyAdCash" selected:
- Show ONLY "Zone ID" field (hide Script URL completely)
- On Save → generate this EXACT code and save in rawEmbedCode:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <script src="//acscdn.com/script/aclib.js"></script>
</head>
<body style="margin:0;background:#000;height:100vh;overflow:hidden;">
  <script>
    var aclib = aclib || {};
    aclib.cmd = aclib.cmd || [];
    aclib.cmd.push(function() {
      aclib.renderAd({
        zoneId: "[ZONE_ID]",  // Replace with user-entered zone ID
        width: "100%",
        height: "100vh",
        onComplete: function() {
          if (window.flutter_inappwebview) {
            window.flutter_inappwebview.callHandler('adCompleted', 'done');
          }
        }
      });
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>

For Custom: TextArea paste → direct save as rawEmbedCode

Test: Save MyAdCash ad with zone 10654258 → rawEmbedCode should have aclib.js (no HilltopAds script)
